One person has been died and several other injured in a road crash at the Nithi Bridge in Tharaka-Nithi County. Red Cross Central and Eastern regions Coordinator Gitonga Mugambi said a PSV bus heading to Meru Town from Nairobi lost control, crashing a few metres from the bridge at about 8:00pm. "One passenger,Â a woman, has been confirmed dead and several injured," Mr Gitonga said. Twelve passengers have been taken to Chuka County Referral Hospital and five to Chogoria PCEA Hospital for treatment. The body of the victim has been taken to Chuka hospital's mortuary. Maara OCPD Johnston Kabusia also confirmed the incident.  